thinking my husband killed someone" dinner.

588
00:36:54,690 --> 00:36:57,020
So alma's alive. Big deal.

589
00:36:57,070 --> 00:36:59,360
We still don't know what went down
between orson and monique.

590
00:36:59,400 --> 00:37:02,140
susan, please. We look stupid enough for suspecting him.

591
00:37:02,220 --> 00:37:03,200
Just let it go.

592
00:37:07,010 --> 00:37:09,670
It may be a little late for that.

593
00:37:09,740 --> 00:37:11,720
Detective ridley.

594
00:37:11,810 --> 00:37:13,120
Can I help you?

595
00:37:13,200 --> 00:37:15,070
Yes. I'd like to speak to your husband.

596
00:37:16,090 --> 00:37:18,430
Oh, well,I'm afraid he's not here,

597
00:37:18,500 --> 00:37:21,190
but I will be happy to tell him that you came by.

598
00:37:21,280 --> 00:37:22,870
who is it, darling?

599
00:37:26,050 --> 00:37:28,310
excuse us.

600
00:37:30,520 --> 00:37:33,670
Can't this wait?We're having a dinner party.

601
00:37:34,440 --> 00:37:36,400
hello, dr. Hodge.

602
00:37:36,440 --> 00:37:37,790
Detective ridley.

603
00:37:37,910 --> 00:37:39,440
We need you to come with us.

604
00:37:39,510 --> 00:37:42,660
We have some questions about that jane doe
we showed you in the morgue.

605
00:37:42,690 --> 00:37:45,490
Why do you think I'd know anything about her?

606
00:37:45,550 --> 00:37:48,910
Well, you were having an affair
with her when she died.

607
00:37:50,140 --> 00:37:52,390
Oh, where did you hear that?

608
00:37:56,760 --> 00:37:58,590
Susan?

609
00:37:59,660 --> 00:38:02,300
I didn't know they were gonna come tonight.

610
00:38:03,910 --> 00:38:08,080
Uh, I'm happy to answer any questions
that you might have.

611
00:38:08,150 --> 00:38:10,010
My apologies. Please, stay.

612
00:38:10,090 --> 00:38:11,900
Enjoy the dessert.

613
00:38:15,330 --> 00:38:17,300
I don't believe this.

614
00:38:17,330 --> 00:38:19,070
You called the police?

615
00:38:19,170 --> 00:38:20,990
Well, obviously,you weren't going to.

616
00:38:21,020 --> 00:38:24,120
They needed to know that that
dead woman was orson's mistress.

617
00:38:24,200 --> 00:38:25,990
I told you that in confidence.

618
00:38:26,070 --> 00:38:30,040
Did you seriously think I could sit on information
that would exonerate mike?

619
00:38:30,110 --> 00:38:33,140
I mean, if you had seen his face
in jail the other day...

620
00:38:33,210 --> 00:38:35,460
the other day?You--you saw mike?

621
00:38:35,490 --> 00:38:39,120
Yeah. I--just to tell him about the lawyer.

622
00:38:39,450 --> 00:38:41,840
I know that mike is innocent.

623
00:38:41,910 --> 00:38:44,220
Right, just like you knew she was dead.

624
00:38:45,220 --> 00:38:47,270
I thought we had an agreement.

625
00:38:47,350 --> 00:38:50,100
We do. Can we talk about this later?

626
00:38:50,170 --> 00:38:51,200
When?

627
00:38:51,280 --> 00:38:53,400
After your next conjugal visit?

628
00:38:53,980 --> 00:38:55,650
Ian. Wait!

629
00:38:55,720 --> 00:38:58,750
Boy, when it comes to mike
there's no one you won't betray.

630
00:38:58,820 --> 00:39:00,470
Excuse me?

631
00:39:00,550 --> 00:39:02,060
Hey, guys...

632
00:39:02,140 --> 00:39:03,620
please leave my house.

633
00:39:03,690 --> 00:39:04,450
Bree!

634
00:39:04,550 --> 00:39:05,890
You heard me. Get out!

635
00:39:06,250 --> 00:39:07,950
Okay, bree,I know you're angry,

636
00:39:08,030 --> 00:39:09,320
